related_questions.question: What can solar energy be converted into?
related_questions.snippet: Photovoltaic energy is the conversion of sunlight into electricity. A photovoltaic cell, commonly called a solar cell or PV, is the technology used to convert solar energy directly into electrical power. A photovoltaic cell is a nonmechanical device usually made from silicon alloys.

answer_box.title: Using solar energy — Science Learning Hub
answer_box.snippet: Using solar energy. Solar energy is transformed into other energy forms for our use on Earth – energy for food (chemical energy), electrical energy and heat energy. Energy from the Sun is transformed into chemical energy, which is passed along in a food chain.
